# Example environment for tests. Copy to .env.test and edit, or export
# the variables yourself. .env.test is auto-loaded by tests/config.py and
# is git-ignored — never commit credentials.
#
# Choose one of the scenarios below.

# ─── Local Docker (default — matches docker-compose.test.yml) ────────────────
# Start: docker compose -f docker-compose.test.yml up -d
# Stop:  docker compose -f docker-compose.test.yml down
#
# All hosts default to localhost, so no env is needed in this scenario.

# ─── Remote VM (klara) ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Uncomment and adjust to point tests at a running VM hosting RabbitMQ,
# Orthanc PACS and PostgreSQL:
#
# CLARINET_TEST_RABBITMQ_HOST=192.168.122.151
# CLARINET_TEST_PACS_HOST=192.168.122.151
# CLARINET_TEST_PG_HOST=192.168.122.151
# CLARINET_TEST_SLICER_HOST=localhost   # Slicer runs on the dev machine, not on the VM

# C-MOVE reachability probe in tests/integration/test_dicom_cmove.py opens an
# SSH connection (default alias: "klara") to test whether the PACS host can
# reach our SCP listener. Override if your VM SSH alias differs:
#
# CLARINET_TEST_PACS_SSH=klara

# ─── Credentials (only if non-default) ───────────────────────────────────────
# Docker compose and CI use clarinet_test:clarinet_test for RabbitMQ.
# Override only if your environment differs:
#
# CLARINET_TEST_RABBITMQ_USER=clarinet_test
# CLARINET_TEST_RABBITMQ_PASS=clarinet_test
# CLARINET_TEST_RABBITMQ_MANAGEMENT_USER=clarinet_test
# CLARINET_TEST_RABBITMQ_MANAGEMENT_PASS=clarinet_test
# CLARINET_TEST_PG_USER=clarinet_test
# CLARINET_TEST_PG_PASS=clarinet_test
